SIMPLE: fulminuric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fulminuric
<hw>Ful"mi*nu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Fulmin</ets>ic + cya<ets>nuric</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to fulminic and cyanuric acids, and
designating an acid so called.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fulminuric acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
white, crystalline, explosive substance, <chform>H3C3N3O3</chform>,
forming well known salts, and obtained from the fulminates. It is
isomeric with cyanuric acid, and hence is also called
<altname>isocyanuric acid</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fulness</ent>⟦br⟧
